entity.description: CNN's chief Washington correspondent, Jake Tapper, hosts this hourlong weekday afternoon program, which covers all the day's top stories from around the country and the world, headlines that span politics, money, sports and popular culture. Prior to joining CNN, Tapper served as senior White House correspondent at ABC News.
